org.gephi.data.attributes.api
Interface AttributeEvent

All Known Implementing Classes:
AttributeEventImpl
public interface AttributeEvent

Attribute event interface, that AttributeListener receives when the attribute model or any attribute row is modified.

  • ADD_COLUMN: One or several columns have been created, look at AttributeEventData.getAddedColumns() to get data.
  • REMOVE_COLUMN: One or several columns have been removed, look at AttributeEventData.getRemovedColumns() to get data.
  • SET_VALUE: A value has been set in a row, look at* AttributeEventData.getTouchedValues() to get new values and AttributeEventData.getTouchedObjects() to get objects where value has been modified.

Author:
Mathieu Bastian
